    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Those Baseball Fans Who Know Only Tears</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bud Stockwell letter comments on John Kenney's humorous Op-Ed article about League Championship Series between Boston Red Sox and New York Yankees (Oct 18)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a lifelong Red Sox fan, I was deeply disturbed by ''Ready for Game 8,'' by John Kenney (Op-Ed, Oct. 18).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a lifelong Red Sox fan, I was deeply disturbed by ''Ready for Game 8,'' by John Kenney (Op-Ed, Oct. 18).</p>
        <p>To suggest replacing center fielder Johnny Damon with Kofi Annan is absurd. The secretary general does not have the range or throwing arm to warrant the change.</p>
        <p>BUD STOCKWELL  Leeds, Mass., Oct. 18, 2003</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
